#X text 513 346 WHEN LAUNCHED: \; - TEXT SEQUENCE OUTPUTS THE TIME IN WHICH FIRST BANG IS RECORDED \; - THIS IS SET AS A DELAY THAT AFTER WHICH FIRST BANG WILL BE OUTPUTTED \; - BANG OUTPUT WILL ALSO "STEP" THE \$0-sequence. AND DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE NEXT BANG TIME AND PREVIOUS ONE IS THE NEW DELAY TIME., f 49;
#X text 699 41 TEXT FILE CONTAIN ABSOLUTE BAR TIME OF EACH RECORDED TRIGGER, f 31;
#X text 508 77 WHEN RECORD/APPEND A NEW TRIGGER TO A RUNNING RECORDED SEQUENCE \, 1) WE HEAR THE TRIGGER DIRECTLY WHEN PLAYED \, 2) IT WILL MESS UP THE CURRENT ON-GOING "TEXT SEQUENCE \$0-SEQUENCE". POTENTIAL CORRECTION IS TO KEEP RECORDED TRIGGERS IN ANOTHER "BUFFER" TEXT SEQUENCE AND APPEND AND SORT THEM INTO MAIN \$0-SEQUENCE AT THE BEGINNING OF THE LAUNCH (TRY LATER)., f 62;
